[url=http://skyrimgems.com/][img]http://static-1.nexusmods.com/15/images/110/4383361-1354321399.png[/img][/url]
[size=4][url=http://semiaccurate.com/][color=#FF5060][b]SEMIACCURATE[/b][/color][/url] did an [url=http://semiaccurate.com/2013/04/17/hialgo-boost-for-far-cry-3/][b]ARTICLE[/b][/url] and [/size][size=4][url=http://semiaccurate.com/2013/05/17/an-interview-with-the-creator-of-hialgoboost/][b][color=#50FF60]ANOTHER ARTICLE[/color][/b][/url] about our tech.[/size][/center][line]
[size=4][b][color=#cccccc][u]Brief description of technology (simplified, an example)[/u]:[/color][/b][/size]

[size=4]The [color=#00FF00][b]GRAPHICS ACCELERATOR (GPU)[/b][/color] is capable of pumping out [color=#FFFFA0][b]"x" megapixels[/b][/color] each second. Lets say this translates into 20 frames per second. This is enough to enjoy the high resolution beauty of Skyrim, but this is [color=#FFFFA0][b]too slow for combat[/b][/color]. So instead - during intense character movement - we draw [color=#FFA0A0][b]3 times[/b][/color] as many frames per second, each frame having [color=#FFA0A0][b]1/3 of the pixels[/b][/color] - so you end up having the same pixel rate, while [b][color=#00ff00]ACHIEVING A MUCH BETTER GAMING PERFORMANCE [/color][color=#FFFFA0]WITHOUT VISIBLE LOSS OF QUALITY[/color][/b].[/size]

[line]

[url=http://www.hialgo.com]HiAlgoBoost[/url] features:

* Significantly improves responsiveness and gameplay experience.
* Significantly reduces in-game loading times.
* Increases framerate during character motion by momentarily reducing the resolution.

Now you can:

1) Play Skyrim smoothly with higher settings, with more effects and mods.
2) Play Skyrim on a laptop with high-end GPU in power-save mode, extending the battery life and preventing GPU overheating and fan activation.
3) Play Skyrim on a laptop with low-end GPU (e.g. Ultrabooks/MacBook Air etc).

***** REVISION HISTORY *****
=============================================================
Updated to version 4.0:
- Now supporting multiple games, not just Skyrim
- Now supporting the latest ENB
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 2.3c:
- Added support for the latest Skyrim version, 1.9 beta
- Improved logging error messages in HiAlgoBoost.log
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 2.3b:
- Fixed 'white screen' artifact for some mods, improved compatibility
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 2.3a:
- Fixed blocking preview in CreationKit
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 2.3:
- Fixed compatibility with ENB, up to v0.143
- Added HiAlgoRegisters.ini to adjust the compatibility with future ENB releases.
- In HiAlgoBoost.ini, added key ALLOW_DYNAMIC_RESOLUTION_IN_MENUS_MAPS_LOCKPICKING,
to allow smoothing and acceleration in scenes like lockpicking.
- Fixed bug that made keys F2, F3 unusable.
- Fixed bug that prohibited HiAlgoBoost from running when TESV.exe was renamed.
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 2.2a:
- Same as 2.20, but changed ini settings to solve dropped frames
on some systems
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 2.2:
- Bugfixes, including ENB crash, vertical map scrolling, etc.
- XBOX 360 Controller support
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 2.1:
- Bugfixes, including "wallpaper replacer" and SKSE FPS counter.
- Framerate drop in static scenes is further reduced.
- Framerate in static scenes will now increase on some systems (VSync workaround).
- Additional tuning and image quality improvements
- VSync is ON by default
- Mode changing is now SHIFT+(HOME/PGUP/PGDN/END), which resolves conflict with SkyUI
- Added a zero cost "fake FXAA" option for lower-end GPUs
- Added INI options for more advanced customization
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 2.0:
- Major update, completely revamped engine
- Framerate drop in static scenes is eliminated (down to 2-3fps)
- Improved responsiveness, decreased lag
- Optimized for image quality
- Flexible configurable of quality vs performance
- Compatible with ENB, ScriptDragon, SkyUI, RCRN, SKSE, Dawnguard, all "Creation Kit" mods, etc.
- Supported Skyrim versions: 1.7, 1.8beta (these are the latest versions)
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 1.34c:
This is a minor update, in anticipation of a major release. Added functionality
is configurable via HiALgoBoost.ini.

New in [KEYBOARD] section:
- All keys in the keyboard are supported now, including numeric scan codes.
- Instant turnaround is now available also by pressing a key ('U' by default).

New in [SETTINGS] section:
- Beep is optional, when toggling HiAlgoBoost on/off with F10.
- Showing popup window on start is optional.
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 1.34b:
- Finally nailed down the nasty bug with shadows - hopefully! Please let me know...
- Fixed another shadows bug after Alt-Tab for nVidia cards. (BTW, after a few Alt-Tab Skyrim
crashes, even without HiAlgo. Beware!)
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 1.34:
-Updated for latest Skyrim version 1.5 (1.5.26.0.5) and for 1.6 beta (1.6.87.0.6)
-Added/restored support for chaining d3d9.dll based mods (FXAA, SMAA etc.)
-Added fix/patch for "green water" bug in 1.5, 1.6 (for some Intel GPUs or when using SAFE_MODE1)
comment: in order for my fix to work, other "green water" fixes should be removed.
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 1.33:
-Added support for the latest ENB v0.112 Kage
-Various bugfixes
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 1.32:
-Added an ini parameter to enable/disable using the middle mouse button for instant 180 turn-around
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 1.31:
-Various bugfixes
-Added SAFE_MODE1 for ATI cards with missing fire and cobwebs, and for other problematic systems.
-Added keys to toggle full/moderate reduction - PGUP/PGDN
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 1.3:
-Supporting ENB and ScriptDragon
-Supporting MSAA
-Supporting NVidia
-Supporting Optimus
-Bugfixes and tuning
-Architectural overall - forget old bugs, expect new ones! ;)
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 1.21:
-removed "demo" status :)
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 1.2:
-support external proxy DLL - both d3d9.dll and dinput8.dll (ScriptDragon etc)
-added FXAA injection
-added Sharpening injection
-added additional configuration keys
-added a "moderate reduction" mode - for those of you with high-end PCs
=============================================================

=============================================================
Updated to version 1.1:
-support winXP
-support external proxy DLL
-better stability
-added configuration file for key mappings
-added a "safe mode"
-added "fixed resolution" modes - x1, x2 and x3
=============================================================

Guys!
I need your feedback! Really! Download, try and comment! I am thinking of doing MW3 next...

Limitations:
You tell me...

Many thanks to DonutAgeOrigins and Waylander1978 for the list of mods that seem to be supported (see below).

HiAlgoBoost dynamically modifies internal rendering resolution in order to increase frame rate, and utilizes various additional approaches to make the game more responsive and smoothly controllable. It does not affect game contents.

Leave your comments and impressions!
